\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Could you give me as your full name?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Shall - have I got to say it in there. Would be all right like that? Yes. I see, you just ask me again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Could you tell me your full name please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Edward Victor Franklin.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And your present address?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Burnt Oak, East Bergholt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And you're a bachelor are you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Could you tell me the year of your birth please?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, I was born 1893. That makes me seventy-seven next June.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And that was in this village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes. Where we told you up at the courtyard we call it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Is it still called that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How many years did you live in the courtyard there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I was there 'til I was about eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You lived there about eight years?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was that when your father moved to buy a farm after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, went up to the Carriers Arms. The pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 To run the pub?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You moved up there with him then, the family moved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How long was he there at the Carriers Arms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Somewhere about eight years I should say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Is that also in East Bergholt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Up the other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 After that where did you go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Then to Coswells farm. We had a lease on that for seven years, well my father did. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you go there then with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You'd have been about sixteen or seventeen then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, I expect I must have been getting on for eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you work on the farm with him there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What sort of work did you do, could you tell me the sort of things you did?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 We
ll - helped him with the - of course it was all horses then. Helped him - well he done biggest part of the ploughing but I used to come what we call the harrows when he drilled and harrowed in. All the cut - and cut the fences down and trimmed out the dit
ches and all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they have sugar beet then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I believe that was an awful job, working the sugar beet.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well I remember when they first grew 'em here, the Dutchman come over here and show us how to grow 'em and how to do 'em, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And it was quite a difficult job was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Oh I've done acres and acres and acres of piecework chopping out sugar beet. Yes. In the - in the - in the summer you know, that and pea picking and all that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 There was a lot of variety and sills weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Oh yes, yes. Yes. See you get your beets, well they're all thick well you've got to cut 'em out and leave 'em about seven inches and you've only got to leave one, you cut all the others out and leave one. Well th
at's simple enough when you get the knack of it but same as you, you wouldn't do anything with it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 It's like trimming a bunch of grapes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. You see we used to hoe, we didn't - didn't pull 'em out you see, just chop 'em and we got the knack and
 push the hoe back, we knock out three or four when your hoe went back and that'd leave one. Occasionally you'd what leave what they call a two. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Would that matter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. The farmer'd come along and say well, you've left a lot of twos. You se
e, you've got to have one. Oh you'd leave - occasionally there's two, you can't do it all - they don't take no notice of a few but - if you get a - 'course that's all piecework you see. We used to do it by acres one time and then it got on so we used to d
o it - the hundred yards. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 
It all made out to the same thing but if they measured your rows up at the field you knew exactly what you was earning on when you'd done a row, how long it took you, you see.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What did they pay you for an acre then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well
 it all depended the land and - some is heavy land well they pay more on heavy land, but if you got light and - 'course they don't do much chopping out now, that's - the drill put 'em so they're very near singled out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you did this it was not for your father, it was for other farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were working with your father was he doing scrap metal collecting then too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. As well. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Had he been in that before he took the lease of the farm or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Well he - he - really started up at the Carriers Arms but all my people have been in the dealing world if you know what I mean. He - he - he started down Flatford at the farm and I used to be with him and one thing and another and I got to learn the trick
 of the trade and when I got older I started.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 About how old were you when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well I started - just before the '14 war. And I continued -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 About twenty-one or twenty-two?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. I - I continued on - 'til I was called up, well I 
went up in 1914 but they rejected me but I had to go again in 1916, in - on March, in March and - they took me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Because they were so much shorter of men then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Yes, yes, I had two - two months training and I was over water to France. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were with your father on the farm - you told me you had two brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Were they older or younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I'm the oldest. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 The one that went over to Andover, how much younger was he than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I think he'd be somewhere about - about sixty-nine now. I couldn't say exactly but that's - that's roughly, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was the other one younger than that or was he in the middle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, well he was next to me. Yes. He went to Canada, I've never seen or heard nothing of him since he went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You say your father's family had always been in the metal trade?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Well they'd been farmers, my father was - a farm labourer before he took the farm but I had grandfather as going in horse dealing, all kinds of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What had your mother's family been, had they also been farm labouring?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Had she had a job before she married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, she's servant. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 After she got married did she go back to work of any kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Women didn't very much did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were living at the Courtyard, was it just your family in the house or did you have a lodger or relations there with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, just the family. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How many rooms were there in those houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
There was two bedrooms I think and - one room downstairs and what they call a back place, backhouse. That's the best I can remember of it anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Where did you usually have your meals there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 In the kitchen, well in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 back place}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your mother cook there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 On an old grate like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you remember what sort of things she used to cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well they cooked different them days, all beef puddings, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 sheep\rquote s}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  heads and all kinds of things, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you have your pudding first before you had the dinner?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes, always, always, always, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When do you think that custom disappeared or is it still going on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 It go in - some - some people do it now - yes, some people do. But that's a thing of the past really, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Why do you think they did it like that, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well I expect that was an old Suffolk way of living you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Perhaps to take the edge off the appetite so people weren't so hungry for the meet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes. Yes, I know I used to like the batter puddings and suet puddings we used to have, well I've had me dinner off that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How often a week did you have meat do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Practically every day. Yes, yes. A little something, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What did you have for breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 We used to generally have piece of cold meat, sometimes an egg or sometimes bacon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you have a whole egg to yourself or did you have to share an egg?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh no, we had a whole egg. Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your mother do the washing at home or did she send it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Oh there's nowhere to go to put it out. Well there was some of the women what was very poor they'd - they used to take in what we call washing but mother always done her own, there was no washing machines then, it was all scrubbed on a board you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Would she hang it out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And if it didn't get dry you had it in with you did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. Then she used to iron it with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 these}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  irons
, I've got one outside somewhere, they used to go on top of the fire then. And - she used to know when they were hot enough then she'd start the ironing. Can see her now, she used to put her hand in a basin of water and sprinkle it on 'em and start.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 She knew just how hot they had to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 She got two, you see, one on and one off you see, when that one got cool the other one was ready.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did she have the one with the thing you slipped in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 She did have one but they were just ordinary flat irons mostly. I've got one outside somewhere, I don't know where it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was she a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 needlewoman}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 , did she saw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, made her own shirts and everything. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did she make your clothes and your brother's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When we were small, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did she ever buy any clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes. But generally used to make practically all the own. Bar same as dressed I expect she bought them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Where did people buy clothes in East Bergholt at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 We used to get 'em at Ipswich.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Would she go to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Ipswich}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. About once a year. Once a year, after harvest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How would she get there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 We used to go what they call a brake and a pair of horses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How long did it take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 About - an hour to an hour and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 She never went on other occasions at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. Later on when I got older she would have went a little more but - my mother never remember the buses, they was all -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 After her time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes, it was all horse strength then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were a boy did you have any jobs to do in the house to help regularly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes, every Saturday when I went to school I used to have to clean the knives, forks and spoons and me mother's shoes and me father's. That was my Saturday morning's work. And chop up a faggot of wood, what we used to call a faggot of wood, for kindling.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 About how much is that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well a few sticks tied up with a piece of string you see and then a bit of firewood and we used to have a chopping }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 block}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  and gather all these sticks up for the week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And the shoes as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How did you do the knives and forks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 On - on a board. On a board, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They weren't stainless steel, the other kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Ay, sharp - they're real steel. Different to what they are now. You don't know the back from the front nowadays. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you enjoy that job or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well I used to really want to be out to play but I used to have to do it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you get any money for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Used to get a ha'penny on a Thursday night, I was in the choir, we used to have a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 ha'penny}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  when we went to choir practice. Yes. Didn't get that if you didn't behave yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did the choirboys get up to mischief?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Who took the choir practice?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 A man by the name of Turnbull, he was schoolmaster here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 It wasn't the vicar's wife who took it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No, no, he's schoolmaster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What sort of things did the boys get up to then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 All manner of things, knock at people's doors and - playing about and one thing and another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You mean knocking at the door then running away?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That's right. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What did they call that round here, did they give it a name, that type of game?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. It's just ordinar
y mischief, we used to get a big old piece of wood if we could and lean it up against the door then tap so when they opened the door that fell in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What other sort of games did the boys play then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well you don't see them, we used to play marbles, hopscotch - what they call woggle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What is that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
That's a thing, you cut it yourself, about that length. A piece of wood, you sharpen both ends like that and we used to call it woggle. And you have a stick and - and hit the end of the woggle an
d it'll fly up you see, being sharp at each end, then we used to hit it. Hit it and knock it up in the air, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was it just each boy play with his own woggle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes, we used to make 'em, we used to - some had better than others and some could hardly cut 'em at all, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Could you cut them well, were you good at that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well fairly, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you have a penknife usually then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What about catapults and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, I had a catapult, yes. And a sling.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 what was that made of?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
That's a - we used to - that's a - you cut a piece of leather out about two or three inches long just so you can get a stone in it, then you got two pieces of string come up and we used to - then let one go. And that used to throw the stone a long way.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you ever get pheasants or anything with a sling in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No, we weren't old enough for that. Had a few since.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Can you get a pheasant that way though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You can with a catapult but not with a sling I shouldn't say. No. That's not accurate enough.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You can get a better aim with a catapult can you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How near to a pheasant do you have to be to get one with a catapult?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 About - you mustn't be much more than about fifteen yards I shouldn't say. Be about fifteen yards, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When did you start getting pheasants and that kind of thing and rabbits?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well I don't know what to say much about that. Really. I - I started to get 'em when I was 
about eighteen or twenty. Rabbits and all kinds of wild fowl or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were a small boy did your father tell you stories or read to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, well my father couldn't read nor write. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did he talk a lot, did he tell stories about things much?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, he was very quiet man. Yes. Lot quieter than what I've been.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did he ever take you out for walks or did you go out with him anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, he didn't - they was at work all day in them days, there's no - when you got home a
t night you was tired. And in the winter you just sit against the fire and have your tea and go to bed about eight.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Because they were up so early weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, my father used to be up at four seeing after the horses.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And weekend work of course too if you were working with horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Oh yes. You'd no such thing as holidays in them days, you never had - eventually they say you had half a day on a Saturday, well that weren't much good to you if you was a horseman 'cos you'd got to g
o and see after the horses Saturday afternoon the same as you had any other day. Sundays just the same, you had Sunday off but you had to be up and feed your horses Sunday mornings and again in the afternoon. You couldn't say, well I'm going out for the d
ay. Well if there's something important you got somebody else to do it for you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 But that wouldn't happen very often?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 It had to be something like a funeral I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Anything like that, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did the men get Good Friday off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No. Never got no holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they have a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Nothing like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did anybody eve try to get one going when you were young?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. Don't remember anything about it, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did that come to the village later or are the men still not in a union on the farms round here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well they are now but it's been so many years back since they joined that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 It's quite recent times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh it's - just in my - I don't know how long it's been going on but that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 
ain\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
 - again so many years back since they started this union business. Never heard of such a thing as that when I was a young man, no. That's just like taxation, you never heard nothing about taxes or anything of that sort. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I suppose the farmer wouldn't have tolerated a union then because they had a lot of men didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well they had more men then than they do now 'cos they was all done by hand. Everything is done by machinery now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did the farmers then treat the men well or not so well on the farms.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Well they didn't treat us so well as they do now I don't think. 'Cos you see in them days you got to go and ask for a job but now they come and ask you. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What about the tied cottages, did many people live in tied cottages?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Some. Some. Some did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Who did the courtyard belong to, the houses there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That belonged to a man by name of - Bennewith.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was he a farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 He had - no, he had - he owned Flatford Mill. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 So those weren't farm cottages at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What was he like as a landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh very good man. Yes. Yes. Nice fellow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did he do repairs if they were needed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You say your father worked very hard so he didn't have much time to do anything in the house, do you ever remember him doing any cooking?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No, he always used to do all the vegetables for my mother on a Sunday morning. I always remember that, yes, always, every Sunday morning. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Why do you think he did it on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well he'd got time. And he always - we never had no pump in the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 well}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 , he always used to draw the water up for us. Before he went to work he'd draw three or four pails of water up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Whereabouts was your well, was it nearby?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, right over - not far off - about ten yards off the house. Went with a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 handle}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  and a chain, you put the pail on and - it's very deep well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Could a young boy pull it up or was it too hard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well - you'd have to be about fourteen I reckon to make a job on it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 So most of the time your mother had to last through the day did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. She could get one if she was pushed but my father wouldn't let her do it. I have got one myself 
you know when I've been about there, she's a bit short.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Where did she put the water when she stood it all day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Outside on the garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You mean when she'd finished with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When he brought it in did it stand there in the back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And she'd take it out as she needed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That's it, yes, with a jug.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 It was much harder work for women then wasn't it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Men - most places they had pumps then, just an ordinary pump.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 She didn't have that though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
We - not where we was there, pumps in other houses, it was - was outside, that was all outside, not in the house. The majority were outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was there much in the way of agricultural work for women then, pea picking or bean picking or stone picking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Stone picking - yes. Some bits of stone picking then, you never hear of it now. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How do they get rid of the stones now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Put 'em on the load. They used to make the roads up with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 In those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. They was all stone, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 So they haven't got so much on the fields now, stones then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Well being so much agricultural work done with machinery I expect that's practically all gone now. There are some but some - some fields have got more than others you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your mother or any of you ever do the stone picking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh, did after I left school. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was that done by piece work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. So much a bushel, I forget how much it was. Not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 A bushel of stones is a lot isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes. Yes. We used to go - only place I went a - a man by name of Hols, he's a builder. His father we used to, as boys, used to go and pick 'em up for or - his son now is over ninety. I used to go - I think he's ninety. Near enough for n
inety. It was his father. And scaring rooks too, we used to have to go and do that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 After you left school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you do it in the summer holidays or the winter holidays too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, we used to have to go gleaning then. 
Gleaning and picking up the corn. Take it home and - some - some big families they used to have a - ground up into flour when they'd finished but my father used to give it to the chickens. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How long did the gleaning go on for, how many weeks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 About - well - used to reckon harvest last about a month to five weeks, all depend on the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 weather}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And then you could go in after they'd taken the harvest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, you see what they call a policeman in the field, there was two sheaves stuck up in
 the middle of the field that hadn't been what they called raked. They used to have a horse with a - we used to call it a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 dew rake}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  and they used to rake all the biggest part on it up, you see. And when - we used to have to - we used to watch this, say the policeman has gone, and off we used to go. You couldn't go there until the policeman had gone.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And they went at different times in different places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How did you feel about the gleaning, would you rather have played or didn't you mind doing it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Well as - as children then didn't have much playtime, you'd always got to go and scrap up a few coppers to help your mother and buy your shoes and all like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you got the coppers did you give them to her then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And it went toward shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Shoes and different things, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 So it was quite hard work for children then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 left}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  school when I was twelve and I was at work - I left school on the Friday and I was at work on the Monday. W
here I - many by name of Kelsey. Colonel Kesley I think his name was. And had to go on the lawn with the iron and take out all the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 plantain}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 , that's a week, take that out. But I didn't reign there long, I didn't like that old man. I finished up there in about a fortnight's time, that's when I went stone picking and all like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Whey didn't you like him, didn't he treat you well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well he was an old Colonel sharp in them days, he always kept ordering you about, shouting at you - I packed that in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your mother and father mind when you packed it in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, I told 'em, they said well you come away.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They didn't want you to be treated like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, no. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you left there you went to different farmers did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You didn't go just to the one farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No. No. Anywhere. And then I went and - I - when I was about - fourteen or fifteen I went and worked - oh what they call Backus Street. I went up to man by name of Wingfield. Wingfield Winnick his 
name was. He was a millionaire and I went as what you call }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 backup}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
 boy, that's to do the knives, forks and spoons and help the gardener in the garden and all like that. And I expect I was there two or three years.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Whereabouts was this man living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I can't tell you, I know the name of the place, now I can't think of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was it far from East Bergholt?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, just - just round - you know where the Lion is down here, you turn round that corner and that's that white house on the left.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 It was quite near then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 So you went on living at home?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What were your hours there, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Used to go at seven 'til five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Quite long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. I used to - they used to give us - give me me breakfast, then I used to go home for dinner and come back again.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And then home to tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Or did you have tea there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, never had no tea there, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I don't suppose you remember what you got paid?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I got about four - four to five shillings a week. All I had when I was turning on that lawn was three shillings. Sixpence a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 At that time was that fairly standard pay for that sort of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. Well men were only getting twelve shillings a week and some ten. A recognize
d thing, two and tuppence and hour. A good many years it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Two and tuppence a day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were staying there was it a big household, did he have a lot of servants indoors and outdoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 There's a cook and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 parlour maid}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 . A
nd - oh there's about three girls there. There's a gardener. I used to - when I'd done me housework, you know, the knives and forks and shoes and - helped do odd things in the house, I used to have to go and help the gardener then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What was he like to work with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh he nice chap. Yes. He's dead now too.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you learn about gardening for the first time there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Well you - you know, you pick it up as you go along when you're boy like that. He told me what to do and - of course he done
 all the hard work and I used to fiddle about with him, 'til I got used to it so I could help better you see. He didn't expect me to do so much. I used to have to work but he done the hardest of the work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you got your wages then did you keep anything back for yourself, did your mother take it all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well only a few coppers if you did. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 
And the whole lot never come to much so you couldn't take much.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What did you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 A few sweets. Yes, and then we used to save up, we used to h
ave what you call a choir outing, save up a ha'penny and a penny a time to - so you had a few }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 shillings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
 when we went - we used to go to Clacton. We used to go then in a brake and a pair of horses to Clacton.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That was once a year was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, onc
e a year in the summer holidays. The schoolmaster what I tell you was in charge of the choir, he - he used to take us, well was in charge of you know, told us where to meet for dinner and all these kind of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What kind of man was he to get along with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh he wasn't too bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They were strict in those days weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Strict, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They used the cane then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, he - he did, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 For what sort of things did he use the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 We used to be up to all manner of mischief. Don't know what we did do. He'd lay it on too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Of course there wasn't sitting home then and watching television was - here?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You didn't even have the wireless then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 The boys had quite a lot of fun then did you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, we was all out - an evening playing you know and that's about the only time we got in the summer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Because you were working all the day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you stopped working }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 here}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  where did you go after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well it weren't - it weren't so long before my father come out of the pub and took the - I don't seem to remember what I done after then.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 After that he took the farm?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I should say he did. Shortly after. But I - I think I helped hi
m a lot about in the garden and done odd jobs and that kind of thing for a time. Then he took the farm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When he took the farm did you work the farm with him then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did he pay you for that or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Three shillings a week and me food.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you think you were better off then or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well I'll tell you what, we always had better food in them days than we do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What ways was it better, better flavour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well, it's better - I mean flour - my mother used to bake her own bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 All her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes. Always baked - there's a place, where as a child at the courtyard is a what they call a bake office there and houses all round, they used to have a day. That'd be your time to bake today and mine tomorrow if you know what I mean.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And they'd go and use it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
That's right, yes. My mother used to bake enough bread for a fortnight, the bread it'd keep then, that was all pure flour then. Used to be done down here, by the wheel just down here, you - c
ome past this morning. That's a rope works now, that used to be a flour mill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was there anywhere people }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 could}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  go and bake a joint?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 The bakers used to do it after they took the bread out if you took it. Charge about a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did many people use that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, several. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 She did hers at home did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did she make homemade wine and beer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Always used to brew her own beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Where did she brew that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 We - we brewe
d it when we got to the farm, we always had it. We used to brew one lot on the other and when one lot was done we used to brew another but there's one more a-coming on. Always had home brewed beer, always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How long did you have to keep it before you could drink it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I don't remember, about a fort - three weeks. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Not so long as wine, wine you have to keep a little longer don't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 She did that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, make her own wine, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Have you done that also?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. I - I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 ain\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  made none this two year, I don't be bothered with it now. I used to make a lot. I know how to do it but the wine they make today it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 ain\rquote t}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  what it used to be when we used to make it out of - they're all new ways of doing it now but that don't come up to the old way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 It's not so good?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Nothing like, nothing like.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you think the beer you used to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 brew}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  was better too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, that's good beer. All the - all the men, they used to have two bushels of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 malt}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
 and so many hops, the farmer used to give them that, all farmers give them that for harvest. So they used to take their own home brewed beer into the fields. 'Cos they - they used to mull the corn a lot then. Used to - what they call the clipper and the 
old sailor then after several years they had what they call the self binder come along. And that used to throw the sheaves out all ready tied. We thought that was a wonderful thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you had that then did you still need people to thatch the stacks?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Oh yes, yes, yes. Oh yes, we used to stack all the corn, they was thatched - it used to stand so long. People what got enough money the longer they kept it the better the corn was. The farmer hadn't got much money he'd soon got to thrash - some use
d to thrash that harvest time, didn't make a stack, and the steam engine come and drum and pitcher and thrash it right off the field. Instead of stacking it stack it right onto the drum you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 At harvest time did you have a feast at all, meat and dancing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
The - the women used to bring their husband's dinner into the fields in them days. Yes. These puddings and potatoes and carrots, all manner of things.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was that every day they'd do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, in during the harvest, that's only time, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Only in the harvest?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well - practically all of them done it but some - some didn't but the majority did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your mother do that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When the harvest was in did they have a celebration at all them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, some di
d, had a - just a day. They used to have what they called largesse spending. When the people like you come and looked at us at work we used to touch them for largesse, they'd give you perhaps threepence or perhaps sixpence or we used to keep all that. And
 we had what they called a day largesse spending, that was in the pub and have a jollification with some beer.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And would everybody give, the people that came to watch the workers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well, majority. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 If a person didn't give would it be considered bad - bad manners not to give?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well they - they didn't think much of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Because the men worked so hard in the fields didn't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Can you remember how long you worked for your father, up until what age? }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 
You}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  went to the war then when you were about twenty-one - twenty-three?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes. Yes. Yes. Somewhere about that. I know I was in France when I was twenty-six. Yes, but I'd been in the Army a couple or three years it must be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you go on in the Army after the war or did you get discharged when the war ended?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No, I done - oh I done about eighteen months after the war. Army occupation up in Germany. Then come back and see - come from there and see the prisoners of war in the camps. There was eighty-five thousand where I was, a place called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Haverhill}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 .
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You went to see them did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
We used to have to take them out to work. I used to be given fifty and I was responsible for them, I'd got to bring the fifty back and see that they done the job as they should do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Were they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Germans}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 ?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You were sort of like a foreman over them were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, well you - have a rifle you know and fixed }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 bayoneted}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  and - they were all right. I got on well with them. Yes. When they got a chap that didn't rush 'em or mess 'em you got on well with 'em. I got on well with 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You didn't have trouble?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well they was like - they was like me, they didn't want to be there, of course they didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Just like English people in a way I suppose do you think the Germans?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you think they worked harder than English people or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I should say they do. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You think they do today also?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. I should say they do. They were all good }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 trades people}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 . They used to make silver nears and - make anything they could, and what they got they used to have to pick up where they could then they'd make lovely things. And it }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 weren\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  one what could do it, the whole lot could do it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 
Now an Englishman, you'll find out an Englishman he's - you'll find one can do something like that and you'll find a lot more that can't, but there\rquote s practically all of them could do it. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Pick up an old piece of tin, they'd make something out on it and let you have it for a couple of fags, you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you learn any German at all, did you pick up any German from them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, not a lot. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How could you give them your orders then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well you could make 'em understand. Yes. A lot of them could speak English. Yes. I remembe
r coming home once on leave and I bought a - it come from France - Belgium, a long pipe with a long stem. Well it's only just for sake of bringing something home and chap see it, he said, well when you come home again do you think you can get me one. I sa
id, I'll try. And after a long time I had another leave and I went to a shop in Belgium and I began to speak the - the Belgium the best I could and this bloke looked at me he say, if you speak English, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 he'd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  says, I can understand you. Yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you came back from the war is that when you went into the metal work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. I started right away. I - I'd - I'd started before the '14 war but I went right - right at it them. For me living.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Before had you done it as a sideline?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Th
at's right, my father used to go to sales and I used to go and then I got so I used to go on me own. He lent me a horse but I bought one just before the '14 war and I - I had to go and I sold that in 1917 I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You sold the horse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was it a good one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 There's a lot to know about knowing about metal I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Could you tell me something about how the trade works?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well - well you see we used to go to sales, well you've got to use your }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 
judgment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  yo
u see a big heap of iron there well you - when you've been at it a few years you think to yourself well - put that down to about two ton. And you can calculate up what you - what to pay a ton for it and what you've got to give for it. You might make a lit
tle bit of a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 blunder}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  and there might not only be a ton and a half and there might be two ton and a half. But I used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You had to use your eye?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I had a - I used to be a fairly good judge, I judged so it weren't many hundred-eight over or under.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You could never have it weighed for you or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, no, it was all collected up at the - what we call }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Micha}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 elmas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  sales. That's in October. Farmers in them days there used to be twenty or thirty sales a year, farmers giving up, th
ey couldn't make a go on it, but you never hear nothing of a farm sale now unless the people die. If the people die you see then there's a farm sale.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Those days it was hard for farmers was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Ah yes. They stick it about two years. Some stuck i
t for years. There all depend what you know about farming and how to go on. Some couldn't make a go of it and some could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 So the farm would be sold up then at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 Michaelmas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  time would it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That's right, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And you would travel round to these farms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, these sales, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 It would be actually at the farm place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
At - yes, on - generally on a meadow across to the farm house. Then they used to have ropes up bring the horses in, all the horses were sold, the cows, the pigs, everything cleared right out. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Were there quite a few other dealers in metal round about?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Oh yes. Yes, yes. There was all one against others, rows and - all manner. Well we used to, of course you don't understand I know, we used to what we 
call it 'knock it out'. Well we used to - we'll say for - there was say six dealers there, we're all in the same metal business. Well you'd hear 'em, they'd come to, what are you going to do? Are you going to knock it out or are you going on your own? Wel
l we'll knock it out. That means to say one buys the metal. Then at the finish, when the sale is over, you see, 'cos if you bid - bid against one another at the finish there's nothing for you nor me nor nobody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And it puts the price up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Of c
ourse it do. Well in the finish come we'll say the buying cost five pound, well the one - start it in rotation and six seven, eight, nine, ten. Well you all keep using your judgement what there is there. Well perhaps - perhaps it'll go up to about fifteen
 
or sixteen pound well then they, what they called the knock outs, they share all this money out amongst you so you all get a - you all get a days work if you know what I mean. Whereby if you all bid against one another and you get riled with one another y
ou'll buy just - just one'll buy it and to finish his lost money just 'cos he would be headstrong to get it and the others never got nothing, nor didn't you, you're money out.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 But you say you would decide among yourselves every time how you'd do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Well it didn't always come off, there'd be a row sometimes about something, somebody had done something wrong and - they'd say well you go your way and I'll go mine. Then of course we used to get stuck into it then when they's a bidding.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You mean you'd fight each other?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes. Well - well there used to be rows but what I mean, we all - say well you can't have it and you keep bidding against them and all one against the other you know. In the finish up with a row or something of that and then y
ou get together again at the next sale and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Be friends again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Were they friends in a way or just people you worked with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well - they all come from different places, dealers used to come out here from Colchester and we used to ge
t one man he used to come from Ipswich, his name was Caterson. Well he was there he'd got a yard where we used to have to take it to, well you couldn't do nothing with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Why?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well he'd buy the lot. He could give more money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 He had a yard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 He could give more than what we could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And he had a place to keep it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh he'd got big yards in towns. Oh tons and tons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did he make the most money in the - field?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, he - he done well. I used to send it over to Germany an
d up the North, whole batch. It's like Greggs, they all used to go up the North. Well if you lived up in the North you could make more of rags than we could here, there's the transporting to get them up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 At this time when you used to go to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 Michaelmas}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  sales, were there rags there as well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Where did you get the rags from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 House to house. Do a village like this, go to every door practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Just getting quite little things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That's right. Then another one says, oh you're round, I've got a sack of rags for you. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Old clothes would they be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes. Old shirts, old socks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you get bones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did do but they got knocked of us as - the Xylonite works down here and all over the place, they made
 the handles with xylonite. They call - what did they call it now - I can't think now. It doesn't matter. Bones, I used to - if you get an old knife - we was talking a little while ago - what'll cut, that's got a bone handle on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You mean the bones were used }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  making bone handles, that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes, yes. All the meat you see they used to - women used to save the bones then we used to go buy 'em off 'em according to what they'd got }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 till}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  we got six or seven hundredweight, then we took 'em int
o Ipswich with something else you see. Then that got knocked off. No good, that's like rags now. No. There's eight shillings a hundredweight but if you had them give you you're money out got to take them into Ipswich, not worth troubling now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When did rags start going out, after the last war}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 , the}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 last}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  time was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, it kept on fairly well 'till sometime, I should say been massed up about eight or nine years now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Is it interesting work, the metal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes, yes, happy life. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 In what ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well your out every day and - when you go to a sale that's more like a bit of fun, you know what I mean.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And you meet all sorts too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, all do, they say, hello, so and so's here today. He'll sharp us up, there won't be much to be given away here today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You knew all the different people and what to expect from them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you traveled from door to door did you have your regular housewives customers you called on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Some of 'em. But 
one - same as this village, I knew where to go to every house where they saved them for me. But in a strange village, well you had to call at almost every door. And I - 'cos I used to make what they call gipsy pegs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What are they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Pegs for linen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Clothes pegs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. I made thousands and thousands of 'em.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Where did you get the wood for that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Down here at Flatford or anywhere where you was - willow. About the size of your thumb. I forget now how to make a - takes several tools 
to make a peg, you wouldn't think that. You see, we used to get the cocoa tins but latterly they didn't have tins, they was in cardboard boxes like. And I used to go round with rags we used to tell all the women keep your - cocoa tins. Well they cuts off 
with a pair of scissors for the bands. We used to get the willow and take all the peel off.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Would it be a very thin}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 strip for the band?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh I }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 ain\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  got one out there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 It's different from the peg you buy in the shop isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes.
 You get a - a peg is about that length and it's like that only thicker. Well first of all you - of course they reach from here to the door the runners and you have a block and you have a piece of wood and you hand - hold like that and then you have a kni
fe here and a mallet and cut them all like that as you go along, all the same size.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 All about four inches long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Little longer than that, about five. And then you used to have these scissors and cut these bands. And then you used to have a tack t
o - piece of tin round and have a hole, make just a little hole in there then tap it in and then you ring it off like that. I've made three gross in a day. Yes. In a day. Four shillings a gross.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You must have worked for hours and hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. I used do it spare time, nights and - if it was a wet day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you find it difficult work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Boring. Boring.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You did it just for the money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Well it used to be our way, they all used to do it. And there was hundreds and hundreds m
ore like me. And when you was in a strange place they'd say, here comes a Gipsy. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Didn\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
 make no difference to us what they called us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You mean because you went in a caravan they thought you were a Gipsy?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You say you'd work at this peg making all day long, you wouldn't have a break for dinner or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No. Keep right on, you - you've got to with piece work. See you, well you do 'em almost like shelling the peas, that's quick, you've got to be quick else you won't earn a penny. Same as now, it take me a month of Sundays to do a gross of them now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You were saying that the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Gypsies}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  are still doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. But not - not much. Not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You'd go to the door then and the woman would ask you if you had any would she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No, you'd tap at the door you see, like come to that door there. Well ma'am, and how are you off for pegs? Well how much a dozen? So and so. Well, I'll have two dozen, three dozen or whatever it was or not today thank you, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What did you charge then for a dozen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Shilling.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you went round to the houses were the people quite friendly?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, well I used to get known a bit, there's a lot of the se people what used to go round you know, they'd swear at people
 and all that kind of thing. Well I learnt it off 'em then, I used to get a - me living practically with me tongue, be nice to people. When they got little children little bag of sweets in your pocket. Ain't he just like his mother or - if he }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 ain\rquote t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  you'd say that to them you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 This man told you this did he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Well I used to see him do it and I got - you pick these things up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you find it helped to be like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes. You - 'cos they'd say after, they'd say, did you see
 that man round here this morning? Oh the insulting old man, I wouldn't buy nothing off him, he swore and went ahead and one thing and another, well - after I'd gone they'd say, oh isn't he a nice chap come round this morning. I used to say 'em I said, yo
u're not obliged to buy anything. I shall be around this way again in about another couple of weeks. And you go through they see you again they say, well, if they didn't want 'em they'd have a couple of dozen when you - they were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Because they got on with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you find you'd stop sometimes and they'd tell you their troubles and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, they'd hinder you a bit. Some'd say, come and have a cup of tea, well you can't - oh I have had a cup of tea but they keep 
us so I shall have to be getting along or I shan't do nothing. And perhaps you get three houses down there's another woman asks you if you'll have a cup of tea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You'd be drinking tea all day long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Were some of them lonely do you think in those days with their husbands out all day long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well they could always find a job in them days, you get young women now go walking round the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Shopping every day and that sort of thing?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They didn't then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. Woman used to go shopping, well she'd get enough to last her three or four days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were doing the metal were you also dealing in horses at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. A bit, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you do that before the war or after the war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I bought some before the '14 war - not many. 1922 I done the most, when I was out - just come out of the Army.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Is there a lot to learn about that too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, there's all manner of dodges. Yes. It's a thing of the past now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 People don't do it now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. Oh horses faked and - you didn't know what you was getting hold on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Could you tell me again about the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Ipswich}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  market?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes, yes. Used to be some funny people there. And you had to watch you step there. 'Course the only thing if you got ha
d you'd got to go out and have somebody else then, that's all there was attached to that, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Some of these horses were very different when you got them home were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Man told me once when I was young, he said wasn't far out, he said, you buy
 a horse at Ipswich market on the Tuesday you'll know more about the Wednesday and that weren't far out either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you get to know the people there and who you could trust with a horse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 But it was part of the job to fake a horse then was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Who did you sell the horses to, what sort of people?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Butchers, bakers - anybody. Anybody.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you ever sell them for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 slaughter,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  for meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I have done, yes. Yes-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Where can you sell a horse for slaughter?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Well used to sell 'em - we used to be Stratford kennels then, they had the kennels there, they used to - they used to boil 'em up and they use to keep the horse fat and sell that to farmers used to have that to put on the wagons and 
tumbrels. They used to take the wheel off in them days, that's thick, they used to put this on with a piece of thin wood and plaster it all round the axle, then put the wheel on again. That's horse fat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I didn't know a horse got much fat on it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, get a lot - that's yellow fat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Like beef really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you sell the horses to the farmers to or mostly to the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 trades people}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 ?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well I never went into big horse trade much. No. Well private people and that. I never d
one so much horse dealing, there weren't so much attached to. You see, you can get a cattle dealer, if he buy a hundred cattle only get ten shillings a piece out of them, well he's made a good day but one horse, you've got to do a lot of lies about it and
 one thing and another, that's hardly worth a thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you had to tell all these lies about a horse you couldn't do it round here because most people would know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, you've got to be fair. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What were your rules then in that way of fairness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well they let a man have a horse for a week. There it is. I've told 'em what's really the matter with it and but they tell you a bit.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You mean to let him have a real chance to see what it's like?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That's it. Well if they're satis
fied they say, oh yes, that'll do me, I'll have it. Or you could sell one to a man and then the next day he says, it didn't turn out like you said it would and I don't care about this and you know what to -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 So there's trouble in it sometimes is there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Were the police interested in what sort of people were doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Yes. They kept an eye on you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you think there were more police to be seen about in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Yes. Was more - indoor wor
k now, writing isn't it. In them days, if you were a big man if you couldn't write your name you'd get in the police force practically.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Were they after the boys quite a lot in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, wouldn't 1st you play in the road then like they do now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they ever punish children at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, they got a pair of gloves and put round your ear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Can you remember how old you were when you started school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Five. Five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What was the school like, can you describe it to me?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well the classes went I think from one, two, three, four, five, up to six I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 All in one room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No. Biggest - three rooms. The infants, they had a special - a little room. And there was one and two, they were together. And the rest was in the big room. A teacher in each of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was it near your home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, I used to have to walk about a mile and a half.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you have to do that when you were five years old?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. Weren't no hot - hot milk and no hot dinners then. Stand 
outside having a bit of bread and jam dinner times, got so far to go home.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You always took a bit of bread and jam with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes. Yes, something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did the teachers punish the children a lot then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They did more than they do now. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you think they were unfair or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Well they done enough to you I think. But you didn't take no notice as they would now. If you - if you went home and told your mother you'd had the cane, that won't do, you'd get it again. Now the mother's come down after the teachers about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your mother ever go down to the school for any reason?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No. If I - I didn't say anything but if I did she'd say, well you must have done something else you wouldn't have got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 If a boy hit you or something would you tell your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 If you did they'd say, well you go and hit him back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 She wouldn't go along and see his parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. Well if there's something done what shouldn't be really done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 But on the whole you'd to look after yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes, you'd got to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did she tell you how you should behave towards your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, well - yes, yes. Used to just tell you to behave yourself and - leave your brothers alone or something like that or -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Because children do scrap don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, we used to fight, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you play with your brothers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Your school, was it a church school or an ordinary board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Just ordinary - well - well I expect you could call church, the person used to come in - once or twice a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What was it's name, was it called }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 Saint}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No, it was only just Burnt Oak school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you remember what you thought about school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I didn't like going for one thing. We - we - I - I left school when I was twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you have a labour certificate to leave then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, we had an examination and if you didn't pass - you had to go 'til you was thirteen and it didn't matter what you was then, you'd lea
ve at thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 But you passed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 My mother and all the mothers they'd say, you do the best you can and - 'cos they wanted you to earn some money you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Would you have liked to have stayed longer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. Didn't want to be there at all. I've learnt more since then than I did there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What did you learn there in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I used to have dictation and - arithmetic. Reading and writing. Used to have singing lessons.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you remember what the teachers were particular about in your manners and behaviour?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They didn't trouble as much then I expect as they do now. They always }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 
liked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  you to have your shoes clean, they'd tell you about it if you didn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What about being on time to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, you'd got to be there in time else you - cop out when you got in there, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 In those days did you ever miss school to do stone picking or was that in the holidays
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. We used to what you call truant in them days. Truant. Bring our - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 
bring}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  a dinner and that as though we 
was going to school and we used to go down the park or down the river. Used to have two or three days what they call on the truant; And then when you went back they'd ask you were you'd been, you'd say you ain't been well or something like that, well-at t
he finish I remember they used to have a book there with a ticket in there, they'd give it to another boy to give your mother. Want to know where you was, well then they found out you'd been on the truant.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Then what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Your dad would that be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, the schoolmaster, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your mother and father ever punish you for anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Give me a smack on the ear sometimes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Ever a hiding with a stick or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you ever remember being punished for anything at home, any particular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
I can remember my father only hitting me only once and the house that's pulled down, it's just down here and there used to be a boy, used to - we used to call him Lanna Foggart, Lanna. And - I used t
o go home to dinner then, that's when I first started, that's when I lived up the courtyard. And they were tarring the bottom of a house, they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 used}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  to in them days, about that height, about two or three feet up. And the men had gone home to dinner and - an
d when I gets over there there's Lanna in this garden stirring this tar. Of course, we used to have a suit in them days, when you'd finished with it for Sundays you had it on a Monday morning for school, then you had a new one for Sunday. He was stirring 
t
his about and all of a sudden he got the brush and daubed me right down the front here with this tar. I went home and my father was - never knew him to be home for dinner time but he'd come home with some faggots of wood that was for the oven to - to bake
 
the bread and everything. Of course I went home and I thought I was going to get this boy into trouble. And - well he said to me he said, what have you been up to? I said, Lanna Foggart done that with a tar brush. So he says, where was you when he - when 
he done that? I said, in Fairweather's garden. He gives me such a smack on the ear, he says, if you hadn't have been in Fairweather's garden that wouldn't have happened. Yes. Always remember that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What did you think when he did that to you then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
I didn't think much on it, it's only - I don't believe I ever knew him to hit me before. He didn't hurt me much. I were only about - oh, six or seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you ever remember him }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 hitting}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  you again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. Mother used to give me a smack to the ear.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you ever get sent to bed without any supper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Yes, yes. Plenty of times.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What sort of things would that before, do you remember anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Some kind of mischief. We got up to so much mischief I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 In those days at the school did the children divide up into little gangs or groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes. Yes, we used to play football and that in the - in the - playground. But we never got a ball, we just - we used to have an old salmon tin. We used to call ourselves the salmon 
tin dribblers. And - I remember - we used to go home when I first started, my mother looked at my shoes she said, what have you been doing to the front of them shoes, you're cutting them all to pieces? I said - I didn't know what to say, I don't know. But
 she found out and I had my orders to leave that job alone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes, well we got a tennis ball then. Used to be a - used to play tennis up at the back of the house there on a big field, meadow and they used to lose some balls there sometimes. We used to go and find one. We used to play football with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That was better then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did the children from one part of the village form a group against another part?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, they used to get to fighting, this Burnt Oak and Strets
 they used to call themselves. Burnt Oaks used to fight us down here, run us home or we'd run them home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They were the two main ones were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did the girls do that too or just the boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Girls didn't fight like boys.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Were there any children that came from the workhouse to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you remember anything about the workhouse?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I remember the workhouse used to be at }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Tattistone}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  here. It's still there but it's turned into a hospital now. You could go in there for a night but you had to do so much work before you come out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 To earn your keep?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you remember anyone going in there at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Remember several. They used to come out one day a month, them what could get out. Used to come back to the village.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What did they think about living there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Couldn't do nothing else. They couldn't see after themselves properly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did people get parish relief then, money from the guardians, when they lived at home, did they get any help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Only what they call charity. That'd be some kind lady.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Who would give money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 It wasn't from the workhouse they would get money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. We used to - what they call - used to be every year, what they call
 calico day. As we used to have to go and get it, there were so many yards of calico for each person. Poor people, only them what were poor. And we used to have a church, they used to have a - a little piece of tin that got Roman figures on it, that was f
or a - a loaf of bread. That used to go on so many weeks in the certain time of year, I forget now. And the baker used to bring this bread and take the ticket off your mother.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Your mother had that did she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And she had the calico?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You don't remember her getting any money from anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No. Well there might be some lady perhaps might have done it but I can't remember. I know they used to - as children they used to behave - big people, they used to give us sweets or something like that sometime, not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Were there quite a few big people, titled people and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Always was a rich village here really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Rich and poor?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Were there people sort of in the middle, trades people, that sort of thing?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes, well there's tradesmen and all like that, they're a little better off than ordinary working man. But I never starved, you hear people say we never had nothing to eat, I always had plenty to eat. My father used
 to kill a pig, all the cottages round here then they used to keep a couple of pigs. Used to kill one and put it all down in the bacon and salt it, you know, had some fresh as well. I never knew what it was to be not hungry. And the food was more wholesom
e than what it is now, it's half poison now isn't it. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did he hang the pig up indoors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes, it used to be killed at home. Well this here man come and kill it. And then he used to cut it up into joints and we used to cook some right away and my
 father he used to know how to do it, he used to put what you call into sweet pickle. Sweet - yes, yes. Uncured bacon they used to call it. Yes. Well it'll keep for-keep - months and months and months.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What about the other pig, did he sell that one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, he'd sell that one, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Where did he get the food to fatten it from, at the mill.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes, at the mill or we used to go round what they call swill then, all the big houses and get the swill where they used to put it in pails outside all the - lot of good stuff in it you know, potato peelings, cabbages.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You'd go round and collect it would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Bits of fat meat and all like that. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they put it out there for the people to collect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, they used to know my father'd go and get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were at the courtyard was your father working for a farmer there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Working for his father. And he died and then of course he went on his own then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was your mother from East Bergholt do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, I think she was born at - other side of Colchester. Marks Tey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you left school you didn't have any regrets about leaving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. I wanted to get away from there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I think most children felt like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They did in them days. They - of course they - they go now and - they've got something to look forward to I think, we hadn't.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 In those days did your mother like you to go to Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, I used to have to go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was that at the church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Church. Sunday school at nine o'clock. Then again at eleven. Then again in the afternoon.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 So it just about took up the whole day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did she let you play or work on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Nobody done any work in them days on Sunday. No farmers done any work. Nothing done at all - nothing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 But did your mother cook though?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, always cooked what we called the Sunday dinner. That's when my father used to do the vegetables.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they go to church on a Sunday or didn't they bother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Didn't bother a lot. I know my father always used to say his prayers, I can - and he learnt me the Lord's Prayer. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Would he say it out loud then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Just say it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did he say grace at meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you remember at the church did they have a temperance club, did they get people not to drink or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That was at the chapel. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you ever go to the chapel too or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh well we went to that to get a - went to the temperance - used to have a piece of blue 
ribbon to show you didn't drink or - you know. Well they used to have a treat, well all the other boys get it and I went about a month before I get to go to this - very well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you have to sign that you wouldn't drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes, yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they try and get a lot of people to join in that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 All the youngsters did w}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 hat they }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 could,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was there more drinking in the village at that time than there is now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes, yes. I mean beer was only tuppence a pint then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your father go to the pub or not?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No, he never - he kept the Carriers Arms after he came out the - occasionally he'd go in this one as we came up here with a load of straw he, you know, he'd say, we'll go and have a - bottle of ale each.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 But not a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, not him, no. If anybody was in there say going to have another one? He'd say, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 no thanking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  you, get back to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They had their own beer and wine they made?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, he'd got plenty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What about your mother, did she go to the pub, or didn't women go then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Well she used to come - there used to be a butchers so up here. She used to sometimes call in for a glass in the morning when she's come up the butchers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 It wasn't considered bad for women to go into pubs in this village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
You know what, you ask me that question, there never used to be no women go in a pub at all scarcely. I tell you what they used to do, they used to have a jug. And you'd see them about nine o'clock at night, they gen
erally used to drink stout, pint of stout and they used to take it home and have a piece of bread and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 cheese}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
 before they went to bed. But as things now there's as many women in the pub as there is men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 But they wouldn't go and sit in the pub?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, just the same as smoking, you never see a woman smoking in my younger life. No. Now they smoke more than men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you ever see a woman smoking a pipe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 There used to be some tramps come in here, an old woman, she used to smoke a pipe. We used to run about a mile to see them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 The children liked to see it did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
So they throw stones at 'em and jeer 'em and - they used to turn round and come back and run after us. That's just we liked - if they'd have kept on going we shouldn't have went much further.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 So when she went to the butchers and stopped for a glass she'd stop in there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, have a glass yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 But wouldn't sit in the pub like they do now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No, no. There used to be what they call a passage, they use
d to go down there and just stand and drink it. I never knew women went to sit down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They didn't have much time for sitting down did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 She had a lot of mending to do and all that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Do her own work like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your brothers also do jobs in the house to help like you used to do the knives and shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 We were all about the same, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 All doing things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How old were you when you first started earning money for farm work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well just after - just after I left school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You didn't do it before you left school, like in the holiday-?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Have done, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your mother ever go out to like a woman's institute?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they have any clubs at the church she went to or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was she one to go and sit in neighbours houses and chat, that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. They used to just have a tale but that was soon all over.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Just when they stopped in the street you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That's right, yes, yes, yes,
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you remember if }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 neighbours}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  called in to your father and your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, they would and - relations perhaps come Sunday night to tea. And sometimes we used to go to theirs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Would you arrange it beforehand?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Or was it just casual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No, no, it would be arranged. Schoolmaster, if you had got a decent voice he'd pick you out and say, you come here and - well you see him. And well, I think you're good enough to join the cho
ir. And in them days you'd got to go, it's no good saying you don't want to go. But I didn't mind.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Even though you had to go and practice it didn't worry you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. Used to go every Thursday night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You said your father didn't read or write, did your mother read and write or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 She could read a little, not a lot, but she could - she could write near enough, you know, for them days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did she ever read, do you remember her reading at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, she'd read the paper. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Were did she get the paper from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 From the newsagent she got it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you have any books in the house or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they ever play games with you when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well, as a little child, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 What}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  sort of games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I don't know, just playing about like I can't say exactly now what it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You don't remember if they played }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 snakes}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  and ladders or ludo or any of those table games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, never had nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they play cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No
. No. I don't play cards myself now. No. I've seen thousands of games played but I never tried to pick it up. I can play or dominoes but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Not cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do the people who go around in caravans play cards much or not more than other people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, they don't do much of that, they're too busy. They're always a doing something when they've been out for the day, making pegs, }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 that\rquote s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  where I learnt how to make pegs along of them. Yes. Always doing something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When was it that you got into the caravan, went round in a caravan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I bought a - the first - first caravan I had was in 1922 I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you did all that dealing with horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Where did you get it from, the caravan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well I bought off a showman. That's a traveling showman what have the fair you know. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What was it like inside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Oh it was - a chest of drawers all made in and a - called hostess stove, it was like this only it had got an oven but not so big, it was all chrome, beautiful one it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And a bunk bed would there be?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes. You fold - done your bed up in the morning after you had got up. And it used to push back. And that made more room in the caravan, it was on a - on a chain and then it used to push it right
 back. That was all designed on there, were all - all designs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you went around in it how far a field did you travel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh - only just about as far as Bury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you stopped for the night where would you stop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Where you could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Could you stop more or less anywhere?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. You weren't allowed more than thirty-two days in one place.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Then what happened after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well you've got to be a going or else the council'd come after you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did that ever happen to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, but we used to stay longer than we should do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Take a risk you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They keep coming after you, say, well we'll give you another day. And you take two or three more.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Why do you think they kept moving people on like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well I expect it was a - the council, is a law like it is now. It's more trouble now to get about with a caravan than it was in then days.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Because of the traffic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And - well, it ain't only 'cos of the traffic, they won't have you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 There's more feeling against it now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. Of course there's a lot of 'em leave such a mass behind and all that kind of thing. Did in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And I suppose people didn't like that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you travel around with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 other people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  or were you on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 With other people, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you work in partnership with anybody or were you on your own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well I used to have a chap once with me - I didn't travel so much as all that. I done a little, not much. I used to make me home here. I
 used to travel along a chap, well we'd go out if we wanted and we'd say well we're standing as we are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 If you got a lot of metal at an auction where would you take it to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 To what you call a scrap yard in any town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 There's one in most towns is there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, there is now. The scrap metal weren't making the money in them days as it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you have to have a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 license}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you ever do hawking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What sort of things did you hawk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Brooms and brushes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you make them yourself too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, no, used to buy them in London. Then we used to take the pegs round you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were a small boy do you remember if your parents belonged to any loan clubs or saving clubs at all or boot clubs or anything?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No, they - we used to be in what they call a slate club. At a pub and that was - you got about six shillings a week if you was ill for about six weeks. Then what was left you shared out at Christmasti
me. That run somewhere about ten shillings, around ten bob, not always the same. Near enough.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they belong to anything for clothes or boots or shoes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well my - my father and mother didn't belong to it but I did when I got so I went in pub.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 To the sick club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You were telling me your mother wouldn't go out very much, not to women's institutes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I don't think }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  was such a thing then. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What did she mostly do in the evenings in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Sit and sew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did she have mending to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What time did your father finish, come back in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh he used to go to bed early, he'd go to bed about half past seven. Especially in the winter, not in the summer. He used to go
 to bed. Well mother didn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were a small boy do you remember if your father was interested in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, not like they are now. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you know what his views were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh he was - he was Conservative, he - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was he active in his support of the party, did he work for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Nothing like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you think he cast his vote or didn't he bother?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh he used to go, yes, yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What about your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I don't think there wasn't votes for women then. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you know if she had an political views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, they didn't study that much in them days. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you ever remember your father having an argument about politics?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. He weren't a man to argue, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 He wasn't that type of man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 In those days some people say that men were frightened of voting the way they would like to vote because of their employers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, well it was some - it was so in some cases. I think. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was that so in your father's case do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No, I don't think so. No. But I've heard it said as how - you've got to vote like your master did or something of that but - then they couldn't tell could they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Nobody could know really because it's a secret ballot?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Have you been interested in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Not a lot, no. I vote, I'm a Conservative. I vote.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Are you a member of the party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was your father actually a member?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No. Oh no, there weren't no - see now they have a dinner and meetings and all that kind of thing, well there weren't much of that in them days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Do you remember when there was an election did the children get very excited?}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, they used to holler and shout, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was there much bribing of people, trying to bribe them to vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You don't remember anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you ever remember a play in the village or a music hall or a traveling circus or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well there used to be a little circus come round. For children more. I went to one when I was about six or seven years old.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did it come every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, not every years. Well I expect it come about two or three times when I was a child. There wasn't much in them days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you ever go to Ipswich to see anything like that when you were a young man?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, I went to Ipswich Hippodrome. When I - I wasn't very old when it was first built. I went t
o first night. Yes, I remember that, on an old cushion tyred bike. Rode from here to there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you go with friends or did you go alone?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Me and another boy, he's still going, he's a little older than me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Is he still in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did he also go into the metal trade?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No. He was a baker by trade.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What did they actually call your trade that you did, what's the actual name for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well - call us metal dealer or general dealer. Well a dealer he don't sta
nd for anything, he'll have a go if he thinks he can see a shilling doesn't he.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you always live here, how long did you live in this house here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I've been here about eight years, seven - seven or eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Not very long?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Before then }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 were}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  you somewhere else in the village?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I was in caravan.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Right up 'til then were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Yes, yes. Yes. Of course I - I shouldn't have come I - I'd rather live in a caravan than I would a house. Only me age was beating me and I mean you're all alone, well you never know do you. That's the reason I hired a house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you're in a caravan do people recognize it when it's coming and kind of know it's your caravan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, they knew.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You had your name up didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I had a name on it, yes. Wasn't supposed to, but you had to have your name on if you was on the road with it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 In East Bergholt when you were a young man you were telling me how there were the big people and then the poor people and you said the }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 trades people}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  had a bit more than the ordinary working class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 In the working class then were there different standards of living or was everybody much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 About the same, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When your father was at the Carriers Arms though was he a bit better off?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, he was a little better off there. 'Cos he used to be out all day with a horse and cart and buying up stuff.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When he was there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Who was serving the drinks then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 My mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And all the housework as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Nobody to help her even then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 She must have worked terribly hard then because the pubs were open all hours then weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Six - six 'til ten.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 She was serving all the time was she.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Well they weren't so busy during the day as night time. You know some come - come - another dealer come buy something }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 right}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  under your nose well you didn't think much of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did anybody ever say your horse had turned out to be a dud?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 At that time do you remember anybody being described as a real lady or a real gentleman by people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, some of the titles. There was one gentleman, I won't say his name, he was called Sir Alfred. He's dead and 
gone now, but that was his name, Sir Alfred. You had to call him Sir Alfred. Well should do, that's how, it was always Sir Alfred.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was there anybody who didn't have a title who would be considered a real gentleman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, he was gentleman just the same. A poor man can be a gentleman, in a sense.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 In those days if people said, he's a gentleman, did they mean the way he behaved too and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 At that time was there a chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, chapel, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What sort of people went to the church compared with the people at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Well both about the same only just a little different religion and what the children were brought up to. If their parents were chapel people well the children went and if they was church of England they went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 There wasn't a different social class or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was it possible at that time if you were a poor person in the village to go up in the world or to come down in the world?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well - some people got on. Some didn't and - practically the same now. Some people get on and some don't. But people didn't get on so}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030  quick}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  in them days as they do now. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were a boy can you remember the sort of things your parents brought you up to think were important or didn't they bother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, didn't say much about anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you remember if in the village there was much difference between craftsmen and labourers at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well there wasn't a lot of craftsmen here, only bricklayers and carpenters and that kind of thing, that's about all there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Would there be a blacksmith?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, blacksmiths here, yes, blacksmiths.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And wheelwright?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they mix in with the other poorer people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Yes. They wasn't so - so well off, oh yes, they all used to meet one another in the pub or something like that and chat.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were in the caravan did you cook all your own food and look after yourself completely as you traveled around?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 We - the chap that I travelled with, his daughter used to always get our meals.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was she a good cook?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Pretty good, yes, yes. 'Course we used to have our meals outside in the summer. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you ever know anybody who told fortunes or was that the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Gypsies}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  like the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Romanys}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  who did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
I know woman what - what supposed to tell fortunes, yes. But that - I don't think take that in. Surprising the fools there is go to 'em and get money though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Who go along and pay for it you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. The seaside in the summer and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 all}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you had the farm after the Carriers Arms, were there hens there as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes, fowls, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And goats at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. My father wouldn't have goats.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Your father didn't like them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Why was that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I don't know. He - he wouldn't let me have one when I was a kid either.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you want one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, and he wouldn't let me have one. I had tame rabbit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And on this farm he had horses didn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 What else did he have besides the pigs and the hens, did he have crops as well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Yes, yes. Wheat, barley, beans.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Can you tell me how many acres it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Roughly about forty to fifty. It's such a long time ago you know. But that's a small farm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did he make a better living from that than he had at the Carriers Arms or much the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well I couldn't say, he had a struggle at the farm. He had to work hard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was it just you and him or did he employ anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
Well occasionally when there was something that he wanted another couple of men he' have 'em, I suppose thrashing he'd have four or five men to thrash - when the thrashing time come.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 But not as a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, no. I used to help him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Just the two of you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your mother work on the farm too?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did she look after the hens or anything of that kind?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh she may have done, fed the chickens or anyt
hing like that, but she never done anything regards seeing after pigs or anything like that. Well I suppose she has perhaps fed 'em when we've been busy or something like that but that weren't here job anyhow.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Your father wouldn't have liked her doing that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did some women do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, there's plenty of women do do it. More today than in them days.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well of course they have more time now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Because the house is easier to run now isn't it than it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did she make here own jam in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did she make pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes, pickled onions, pickled cabbage, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When you were in the farmhouse did you have more rooms there than you'd had at the courtyard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, it was very small place. There was two bedrooms and a little living room and what we call the backus.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Can you think of anything particular that happened there at the farm or the Carriers Arms?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. Only what I've told you. I - I say I must have told you everything really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 When people used to come to the Carriers Arms were you old enough, were you allowed into the pub then to meet the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I - I weren't old enough but I used to be in there. Yes. I used to have a drop of beer too.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 They used to stand you a drink did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they talk to you and that kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 How old were you supposed to be to go in then, was it eighteen then like now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Fourteen.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you remember a funeral before the end of the first war at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh I remember several. The same churchyard now as what it was then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they make more fuss at a funeral then than now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. About the same as usual.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you or your father take part in any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No. No. No. No, we used to play quoits at the pub - out - outside quoits. Steel quoits. Oh yes, steel quoits yes. When I got old enough I used to play. And we used to play what they call }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 
parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  quoits inside, a board with just numbers on. Parlour. Parlour quoits we used to play. That's a square board about that square with numbers on and there was a middle, fifty.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 And you had to try and ring the middle one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 That's it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You didn't play cricket or football?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. We played football as a child but not - not play football when I got older. They had a football team here. Oh yes, but I didn't play.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they have a cricket club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. And tennis.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was it just for the sort of gentleman type person or could anyone join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh anybody could join, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your father play sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You were interested in horses, did you go to the races and bet on horses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, I went to the Derby nine years righ
t off. The last one I went to was the coronation - Coronation Derby. And that's when Gordon Richards won his first Derby. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 Yes, I can tell you the horse's name, Pinza. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I didn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you have a bet on it?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No, I didn't back it, we had a busload g
o from here and I told 'em there, I said, he never did win a good race, nor he never did. I said, he won't win the Derby, I said, it's his last one, I said, he won't win it. But he did. He did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did any of them win big winnings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, some of 'em yes. I didn't do it, I done a loser.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did you bet on dogs, greyhounds at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I have but not much. I have but not much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. There was no dog races when he was about. NA.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 There was horse racing though wasn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Was he interested in that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Not a lot. He was no scholar you see. All his interest was in work. He was - he was more happy at work than he would be at pleasure.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did he enjoy the work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. Yes. That's all he thought about, work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Had he always been like that do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 As far as I know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 He'd always done farm work had he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did he ever go and work in people's gardens as well to get extra money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Have you done that at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I have done since I've been a pensioner. I've gone and done a few hours but I can't do it now. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 It\rquote d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  be very handy, I've got to live like on the pension now and that }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14486858\charrsid1012030 isn\rquote t}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  much. I used to go and knock up perhaps a couple of poun
d or fifty bob, well that was handy. I've done a lot of sugar beeting since I've been on me pension when I was about - when I was turned sixty-five, I could do it then. But as I got seventy I began to go downhill but I still carried on 'til about three ye
ars back, but can't do. I've got a little garden out here of me own, I do that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do you grow enough fruit and vegetables for yourself or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Grow enough in the summer. Plenty - peas and beans and potatoes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 You didn't have any savings from your work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 
No, used to spend as I went along. I had to have some money when I was buying the different things. I got some money then but that all dwindled.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did people borrow from each other in the trade then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Well have done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Have you ever had anything to do with }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12409986\charrsid1012030 pawn broking}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030  at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 No. No, I never pawned anything in me life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Did they have one at Ipswich?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Oh yes. One there now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10444528 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 Do they do much business now do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5458979 EF  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13645478\charrsid1012030 I think so.
\par }}